Ahead of the 2023 election, Kano State Governor, Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has issued a 24-hour ultimatum to any political appointee seeking to contest elective positions to resign. In a three-paragraph- statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Abba Anwar, Ganduje ordered that such appointees should leave on or before Monday 18th, April 2022. According to him, ” all political appointees running for elective offices in the forthcoming 2023 general elections are to resign from their respective positions.“They are given between now to Monday 18th April 2022, to resign. The directive is pursuance and or, compliance to section 84 (12) of the newly amended Electoral Act,” Anwar said in the statement.